<item>
            <title>[WICKET-4890] Bad validation messages after WICKET-2128</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/WICKET-4890</link>
                <project id="12310561" key="WICKET">Wicket</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In most languages (at least the ones that I speak), the error messages used by validators don&apos;t sound right anymore after &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/WICKET-2128&quot; title=&quot;StringValidator error messages erroneously mention input instead of label&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;WICKET-2128&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;WICKET-2128&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; was fixed. Replacing &apos;${input}&apos; with &apos;${label}&apos; (what seems to have been done) doesn&apos;t yield useful error messages.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I see the following options:&lt;br/&gt;
a) Improve the messages the way Martin Grigorov suggested it in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/WICKET-2128&quot; title=&quot;StringValidator error messages erroneously mention input instead of label&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;WICKET-2128&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;WICKET-2128&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, e.g.&lt;br/&gt;
&apos;IConverter=The value of &apos;${label}&apos; is not a valid ${type}.&apos; &lt;br/&gt;
(instead of just &apos;IConverter=&apos;${label}&apos; is not a valid ${type}.&apos;)&lt;br/&gt;
Interestingly, all the languages that use .xml properties (e.g. Application_bg.properties.xml) files seem to have been excluded (by accident?) from the changes done in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/WICKET-2128&quot; title=&quot;StringValidator error messages erroneously mention input instead of label&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;WICKET-2128&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;WICKET-2128&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, as they still refer to ${input}.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;b) revert the changes from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/WICKET-2128&quot; title=&quot;StringValidator error messages erroneously mention input instead of label&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;WICKET-2128&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;WICKET-2128&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; completely. I think the new messages only fit well in scenarios where there&apos;s only a single feedback panel per page, which is anyway not very userfriendly. In cases when you display the error messages in separate feedback components next to the corresponding FormComponents, it is anyway clear which field is the culprit, and users don&apos;t need to search for the field that has caused the error.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
